722258f-b.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 53rd Street
722258f-b.text:
Park Averue, north on west side, from 53rd to 57th Streetg.showing
the block of small buildings much older than their surroundings.
Compare with Ewing Gallowey's photographs of Park Avenue north
from 52nd Street in 1905 and in 1932.
Note construction Poing on in 53rd street; s branch of the new
municipal subway is being tunnelled under 53rd Street.
April 3, 1928.
P.L. Sperr, Photographer.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
The same, showing a view farther north. The block of small old houses
from East 53rd to East 54th Streets has been replaced by a one-story
building to be used for stores.
February 7, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
